The paper focuses on improving data management systems with learned components, specifically learned index structures. This topic falls under the database (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper proposes a new benchmarking framework to compare learned indexes against traditional index structures, which further supports the relevance to these sub-categories.
